**Biographies:** Guy MELARD is Professor of Statistics and Computer Science, Faculte des Sciences sociales, politiques et economiques, and Institute of Statistics and Operations Research, Universite Libre de Bruxelles, Belgium. He has published articles in the _Journal of Time Series Analysis_, _Journal of the American Statistical Association_, _Journal of Forecasting_, _IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing_, and _Annals of Statistics_. He has written a book on short-term forecasting methods and has developed many algorithms for computational statistics. His research interests include theory and applications of time series analysis and forecasting.

Jean-Michel PASTEELS was Teacher Assistant at the Department of Applied Economics (DULBEA), Universite Libre de Bruxelles, where he obtained a PhD in Economics. He has published articles in the _Cahiers du Centre d'Etudesde Recherche Operationnelle_ and _Cahiers Economiques de Bruxelles_. He has developed, in collaboration with the first author, an expert system for time series analysis. His research interests include theory and applications of time series analysis, economic forecasting, expert systems and international trade theory. He is presently 'Trade Analyst' with the United Nations in Geneva, Switzerland.